OL,6,FIf you know any parents of babies or
OL,7,Fyoung children, you'll no doubt have
OL,8,Fheard them tell you about the one
OL,9,Fthing they miss the most from pre-
OL,10,Fparent life ` sleep.
OL,12,FIn the first few months of life, a
OL,13,Fbaby will wake up to be fed very
OL,14,Foften: around every 3-4 hours. At
OL,15,Fthat stage, there's no escape for
OL,16,Fparents: they just have to wake up
OL,17,Ftoo. But as babies get older and
OL,18,Fapproach six months, they'll often be
OL,19,Fable to sleep for long stretches `
OL,20,Feven, for some, all night.
OL,3,CShould you sleep train your baby?
OL,4,CHere's what the science says
